  <data name="Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Frequently Asked Questions</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Q1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>How exactly is the animation laser show performed?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="A1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>A high-tech laser projector projects vibrant, dynamic graphics and storyline animations onto a special semi-transparent mesh screen in perfect synchronization with the music. This creates a stunning illusion of a 3D image floating in mid-air.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Q2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Can the animation show be performed outdoors?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="A2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Storyline animation shows are performed primarily indoors. This is because projection requires a special tension mesh screen that is sensitive to strong wind gusts. However, in calm, windless weather, projecting directly onto a flat building facade is possible.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Q3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Is it possible to develop a custom script and choose our own music?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="A3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Absolutely! We can create a unique laser love story, a spectacular brand presentation, or a custom festive show based on your personal script, set to any music of your choice. Every detail of the video is coordinated with you step-by-step during the production process.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Q4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>How much time is needed to prepare the laser show?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="A4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>If you choose a standard program from our library (e.g., classic wedding, New Year, or graduation theme), preparation takes 2 to 5 days. Creating a fully custom animation video from scratch based on your requirements requires 2 to 4 weeks of meticulous work by our animator.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Q5" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Is a fog or haze machine used during the performance?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="A5" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Yes, for a spatial beam show, having a light haze in the air is critical, as it makes the laser beams visible and spectacular. We use professional, safe haze generators (hazers). We always pre-coordinate their usage with your venue's management.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="A6" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>A beam show is a powerful spatial performance. It is typically used as a spectacular musical interlude, a grand climax of the event, a dynamic opening for the dance floor, or to brilliantly highlight key moments of the entertainment program and contests.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Q7" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Which is better for a wedding: a beam or animation show?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="A7" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>It depends on your goals. If you want to tell a touching and romantic story of how you met — a graphical animation show on a screen is the ideal choice. If you want to spectacularly enhance the newlyweds' first dance or energize the dance floor — a beam show will create an incredible, magical atmosphere. For the ultimate impact, we recommend the combined option.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Q6" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>How is the beam show conducted at an event?</value>
  </data>
